Call `@testing` in Cursor Composer before committing each screen. No globs — manual only.

## Screen Smoke Check

Before committing any screen, verify all of the following:

### Render
- Component renders without errors in default state
- No console errors or warnings in default state
- All required props are passed — no TypeScript errors

### Interaction States
- Default state: renders correctly with real data from seed
- Loading state: `SkeletonBlock` or `SkeletonText` renders (never null, never blank)
- Error state: `ErrorBanner` renders with retry action where applicable
- Empty state: `EmptyState` renders with title and message (never blank space)
- Disabled state: buttons show `opacity: 0.5`, `cursor: not-allowed`

### Data Variables
- All dynamic variables inject correctly with real seed data values
- No `undefined` renders as visible text
- Nullable fields have defined fallback rendering (not blank)
- No lorem ipsum or placeholder copy anywhere on screen

### Copy
- All copy in Vietnamese — no English visible to users
- No `!` anywhere in copy
- Protocol format correct: `[Tên bài] · [Thời lượng] · [Địa điểm]`
- AI response copy: does not start with forbidden openings, does not end with forbidden closings

### Navigation
- Enters from the correct screen via the correct trigger (per screen spec)
- Exits to the correct screen via the correct trigger (per screen spec)
- Back behavior matches spec (hardware back / disabled / navigate to correct parent)
- Deep links resolve correctly where applicable

### Mobile Viewport
- Renders correctly at 375px width (iPhone SE baseline)
- No horizontal overflow
- All touch targets ≥ 44px height
- Bottom nav does not overlap content

### Tokens
- No raw hex values in style props
- No raw pixel values in style props
- All colors reference `colors.*` tokens
- All spacing references `spacing.*` tokens
- No `!important` anywhere

### Auth
- Anonymous session: screen works without JWT (if applicable per spec)
- Protected screen: redirects to onboarding if no session
- JWT not present in localStorage or sessionStorage (verify in DevTools → Application)

### Log Amendment
If any deviation from spec is discovered during this check:
- Add one row to `amendments-log.md` — takes 30 seconds
- Do NOT edit the spec during the build session
- Tag as BLOCKING if it prevents building the next screen
